<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1779,2022]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1816,1842]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks.</emphasis>
The alternating lifecycle was closed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[771,1069,1815,1842]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and the sexual and asexual generations were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[458,641,1851,1878]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="838 - 843" refId="ref44942" refString="Ide, T., Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y. (2010) Discovery of a new Plagiotrochus species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) inducing galls on the evergreen oak in Japan. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 103 (6), 838 - 843. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / AN 10101" type="journal article" year="2010">
Ide 
<emphasis box="[500,549,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1779,2022]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,356,1887,1914]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[363,662,1887,1914]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
numbered the gall of the sexual generation as C-056 and the gall of the asexual generation as C-052. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[523,703,1923,1950]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="838 - 843" refId="ref44942" refString="Ide, T., Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y. (2010) Discovery of a new Plagiotrochus species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) inducing galls on the evergreen oak in Japan. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 103 (6), 838 - 843. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / AN 10101" type="journal article" year="2010">
Ide 
<emphasis box="[566,615,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
described a new species, 
<emphasis box="[992,1123,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ide, Wachi &amp; Abe" authorityYear="2010" box="[992,1119,1923,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Plagiotrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masudai">P. masudai</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1779,2022]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1959,1985]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Biology.</emphasis>
The bud galls of the sexual generation and the integral twig galls of the asexual generation both develop on 
<taxonomicName box="[255,366,1995,2022]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis box="[255,366,1995,2022]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Q. glauca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[440,627,1995,2021]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cyclobalanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[440,627,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Cyclobalanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[750,916,1995,2022]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="838 - 843" refId="ref44942" refString="Ide, T., Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y. (2010) Discovery of a new Plagiotrochus species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) inducing galls on the evergreen oak in Japan. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 103 (6), 838 - 843. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / AN 10101" type="journal article" year="2010">
Ide 
<emphasis box="[792,842,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
